WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.080 --> 00:00:01.497
Hey, good morning family.

00:00:01.497 --> 00:00:03.300
How are you all doing today?

00:00:03.670 --> 00:00:08.600
I have my wife with me again, my companion, my friend.

00:00:09.040 --> 00:00:09.429
We're excited.

00:00:09.429 --> 00:00:19.860
We're going to talk to you all about hearing the voice of the Lord and following the peace of God in your life so that you can hear Him for yourself.

00:00:20.620 --> 00:00:23.010
The Holy Spirit is no respecter of persons.

00:00:23.010 --> 00:00:24.080
The Lord is not.

00:00:24.080 --> 00:00:34.000
And I believe with all my heart that He wants you to live a good life, to live a life full of abundance to the full until it overflows.

00:00:34.347 --> 00:00:41.760
We don't have to struggle spiritually, physically, financially, mentally, or emotionally in any area of our life.

00:00:41.760 --> 00:00:43.680
He wants us to be successful.

00:00:44.224 --> 00:00:51.610
You know, we get a lot of people emailing us on a day-to-day basis asking, 'Hey, can you hear the Lord for me?

00:00:51.610 --> 00:00:54.568
Can you tell me where I'm supposed to invest my money?

00:00:54.568 --> 00:00:59.947
Can you tell me if I'm supposed to move or if I'm supposed to buy a new car?

00:00:59.947 --> 00:01:03.616
' It's amazing the emails that we get.

00:01:04.624 --> 00:01:10.046
I see the lack in the body of Christ of hearing the voice of God for themselves.

00:01:10.046 --> 00:01:14.800
The prophets of old, they heard for the world.

00:01:14.800 --> 00:01:25.079
They heard what was coming because the Holy Spirit didn't dwell in each individual person yet, since Jesus hadn't died on the cross.

00:01:25.079 --> 00:01:31.200
When He died on the cross, He came and He lives on the inside of every believer.

00:01:31.200 --> 00:01:39.119
The moment you receive Jesus Christ as your Lord and Savior, you have your wall-to-wall Holy Ghost.

00:01:39.119 --> 00:01:41.010
He dwells on the inside of you.

00:01:41.653 --> 00:01:44.031
It's exciting as a believer.

00:01:44.031 --> 00:01:45.119
That's right.

00:01:45.119 --> 00:01:50.159
And it's for a child too.

00:01:51.617 --> 00:01:58.320
The moment a child asks Jesus Christ to be the Lord and Savior, they have the ability to hear the Lord.

00:01:58.320 --> 00:02:05.029
He didn't make it hard; we make it hard by trying to complicate it with our thoughts.

00:02:05.720 --> 00:02:10.776
I don't know; maybe I've developed a different kind of relationship with the Lord.

00:02:10.776 --> 00:02:20.343
It seems like in my life, because I've had so many challenges with my learning, I believe maybe there's a lot of simplicity in that.

00:02:20.343 --> 00:02:33.111
It's because I always stick with being like a child because in my mind, having learning disabilities and all the things that I've gone through in life, I've had to trust Him.

00:02:33.111 --> 00:02:41.502
I've had to get down inside every single day and say, 'Lord, help me,' because of the things that I've overcome.

00:02:41.502 --> 00:02:49.146
Maybe if you have a genius IQ, you try to rely on your more intellectual self all the time to get through life.

00:02:49.146 --> 00:02:52.319
You feel you don't have to have the Holy Spirit.

00:02:53.577 --> 00:03:03.599
I think that intellect can sometimes get in the way of your relationship with God because if you overthink things, it's supposed to be very simple and very childlike.

00:03:04.720 --> 00:03:07.978
You just come to Him and say, 'God, I need you.

00:03:07.978 --> 00:03:11.640
I want to sit at your feet today; tell me what's on your heart.

00:03:16.280 --> 00:03:18.030
Lead me and guide me today.

00:03:18.030 --> 00:03:31.840
' Every day you wake up and say, 'Father, I come to you today and I thank you that you lead and guide me in everything I do and every step I take, that it's all of you and none of me.

00:03:31.840 --> 00:03:36.000
' Sometimes we overcomplicate it.

00:03:36.640 --> 00:03:44.879
I believe a lot of people think that you have to have a certain method; it has to be like algebra, and it's not.

00:03:48.229 --> 00:03:53.360
A lot of believers always ask, 'What's the difference between my thoughts and the Holy Spirit?

00:03:53.360 --> 00:03:54.319
' They ask that all the time.

00:03:54.319 --> 00:03:56.880
'How do I know it's the Holy Spirit speaking to me?

00:03:56.880 --> 00:04:02.560
' He is the one that has the peace that passes all understanding.

00:04:02.560 --> 00:04:03.828
It's that inward peace.

00:04:05.096 --> 00:04:08.159
If you follow your peace...

00:04:08.159 --> 00:04:19.119
I was talking to you all a couple of videos ago about how when I talk to somebody on the phone or I'm around somebody, the Holy Spirit instantaneously tugs at my heart.

00:04:19.119 --> 00:04:23.040
I do not hear an audible voice like I'm talking to my wife right now.

00:04:25.216 --> 00:04:26.600
The Holy Spirit doesn't speak like that.

00:04:26.600 --> 00:04:29.726
He speaks in that still, small voice, and I follow that peace.

00:04:29.726 --> 00:04:39.439
If he says in my spirit that person right there has ill intentions for you, he automatically speaks inside of me to warn me.

00:04:41.440 --> 00:04:43.679
Or say I want to go and buy a mega-house.

00:04:48.937 --> 00:04:59.920
You think, 'Well, God supplies all my needs according to His riches in glory by Christ Jesus, and God's just going to provide for us and we're just going to go out and buy a million-dollar house today.

00:04:59.920 --> 00:05:02.853
' That could be presumptuous.

00:05:03.280 --> 00:05:11.154
You can get real fleshy and weird by trying to follow the peace and thinking, 'Well, I can afford it because God's going to provide for me,' but you have that inward tug saying, 'Don't do that.

00:05:13.257 --> 00:05:13.989
That's foolish.

00:05:13.989 --> 00:05:15.006
Don't do that.

00:05:15.006 --> 00:05:17.920
' That's the Holy Spirit trying to lead you and guide you.

00:05:18.400 --> 00:05:23.500
In the natural, you can believe God for more, but you need to stay where your faith is at.

00:05:23.500 --> 00:05:29.380
If you can't believe God for five dollars, how do you think you're going to believe God for a million?

00:05:29.380 --> 00:05:36.720
You've got to learn how to take your baby steps by faith every single day and grow it like you go to the gym.

00:05:36.720 --> 00:05:45.303
You work out and you're lifting weights, and you increase that weight every couple of months.

00:05:46.309 --> 00:05:48.080
You get stronger and stronger.

00:05:50.320 --> 00:05:56.560
Eventually, you're going to be able to lift a lot more than what you did when you first started.

00:05:56.560 --> 00:05:58.976
But you've got to take it a day at a time.

00:05:59.160 --> 00:06:06.992
I think a lot of people start acting weird or flaky because they're impatient.

00:06:06.992 --> 00:06:08.960
It takes development.

00:06:09.636 --> 00:06:14.640
Back in the sixties and seventies, mom used to tell me about it.

00:06:17.320 --> 00:06:17.520
You used to have the one-hour MotoPhoto.

00:06:19.142 --> 00:06:21.520
That was when we were kids.

00:06:21.520 --> 00:06:28.009
You could go and get your pictures done within an hour, and we were excited to get those in an hour.

00:06:29.982 --> 00:06:35.900
At first, it took about a week to go get your pictures done at Walmart or at the Kodak store.

00:06:43.931 --> 00:06:44.217
They had some kind of development center where you take your film.

00:06:56.639 --> 00:06:56.788
It took time, a process of developing those pictures.

00:06:56.788 --> 00:06:57.920
Then they came out with Polaroids.

00:06:57.920 --> 00:07:01.942
You'd see things being developed really fast in front of your face.

00:07:01.942 --> 00:07:11.551
When I was a little boy, they got those Polaroid pictures and grandma would take them for our birthdays.

00:07:11.551 --> 00:07:17.120
She'd hand you those photos and we got so accustomed to wanting things so quickly.

00:07:17.120 --> 00:07:18.427
We want it right now.

00:07:20.320 --> 00:07:20.640
There's a process of development.

00:07:20.640 --> 00:07:25.119
Whenever you're taking a picture of your life and you look at yourself, you change.

00:07:25.119 --> 00:07:28.720
We go from glory to glory, but we have to be patient.

00:07:29.359 --> 00:07:30.319
There are no shortcuts.

00:07:30.319 --> 00:07:34.419
Now we're used to the iPhone click and it's there.

00:07:34.419 --> 00:07:39.070
You can download it and send it to Australia in seconds.

00:07:45.040 --> 00:07:46.526
It doesn't take any time at all because we're so accustomed to having it right then.

00:07:46.526 --> 00:07:50.139
But there is a development in the spirit.

00:07:50.139 --> 00:07:54.366
There's a development in your walk with Jesus that takes time.

00:07:54.366 --> 00:08:00.319
It is not something that you're going to get overnight.

00:08:00.319 --> 00:08:02.586
It is a trial.

00:08:02.586 --> 00:08:10.613
There is a refiner's fire that comes with your development, walking with Jesus, hearing Him, knowing Him intimately, and following His voice.

00:08:10.613 --> 00:08:13.707
It's a development like the old way you did your film.

00:08:14.500 --> 00:08:21.180
And the Bible says if you seek, He'll knock, and Seek ye first the kingdom of God.

00:08:21.180 --> 00:08:24.640
Knock, and the door will be opened to him.

00:08:24.640 --> 00:08:25.712
Seek, and you shall find.

00:08:25.712 --> 00:08:28.760
I believe with all my heart that people are wanting that instantaneous drive-thru Christianity.

00:08:28.760 --> 00:08:38.660
They want to hit you in the head with a cheeseburger as you drive by because you don't even want to chew it up anymore.

00:08:38.660 --> 00:08:47.160
Open the window, the carhop goes at you and hits your head, and you keep driving because you don't even want to chew.

00:08:47.160 --> 00:08:51.805
We've got to slow down and realize that development with Jesus takes time.

00:08:51.805 --> 00:08:59.839
Just like anything worth doing is worth doing well and doing right.

00:08:59.839 --> 00:09:05.280
Following that still, small voice in your day-to-day life is key.

00:09:14.640 --> 00:09:15.000
If you have a check, follow that peace that passes all understanding.

00:09:15.000 --> 00:09:27.093
If somebody comes up to you and says, "Listen, I've got this investment opportunity for you," and you instantaneously have a feeling of irritation—it just weighs heavy and doesn't feel right—you know there's something not right about it.

00:09:27.369 --> 00:09:33.872
You could study it, but the Holy Spirit could be leading you to have peace while you reason in your mind.

00:09:34.480 --> 00:09:37.220
You feel a prompting in your spirit to do something, but you reason yourself out of the blessing because you try to add your intellect to the things of the Spirit.

00:09:38.420 --> 00:09:43.030
You can't do that because He sees more in the future than what you know of your past.

00:09:47.720 --> 00:09:55.360
He knows the great inventions and creative ideas to get wealth, but you will reason in your mind and cause a complete meltdown because you're trying to think, "Is this really God?

00:09:55.360 --> 00:10:09.909
" When you have that peace and that green light, but then you say, "I don't feel like I should do this," you're using your intellect to try to navigate through the Spirit.

00:10:18.640 --> 00:10:19.635
You can't do that.

00:10:19.635 --> 00:10:25.200
You have to get in the Spirit when it comes to hearing Him and get out of your flesh.

00:10:27.874 --> 00:10:38.720
Say you're dating somebody and you feel this person is the cat's meow, the best thing ever, but then you feel a check about that person.

00:10:38.720 --> 00:10:41.010
The Lord is telling you not to marry them.

00:10:41.340 --> 00:10:48.640
You're like, "Well, they look so handsome or beautiful, and I really feel this is God.

00:10:48.640 --> 00:10:51.566
" But you're looking at the outward appearance.

00:10:51.566 --> 00:10:58.480
They are just really nice-looking people, and you start questioning that inward check because the Holy Spirit said, "Don't marry them.

00:10:58.480 --> 00:11:02.937
" You don't see the intent of their heart; this is going to wind up in a disaster.

00:11:03.394 --> 00:11:08.240
He's warning you: "Do not be unequally yoked with an unbeliever.

00:11:12.600 --> 00:11:12.780
" You might think, "I can get them saved; we can date and I'll get them saved.

00:11:13.680 --> 00:11:19.074
" You think after a couple of dates, if you lead them to Jesus, then they'll be a Christian and everything will be alright.

00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:28.880
But the Bible strictly says, "Do not be unequally yoked with an unbeliever.

00:11:29.737 --> 00:11:31.211
" The Word is already guiding you.

00:11:33.200 --> 00:11:36.079
That's the ultimate voice—the Word of God.

00:11:36.640 --> 00:11:40.959
If the Word says it, that's all you need to know.

00:11:42.239 --> 00:11:49.632
Read the scriptures; look things up about marriage or finances.

00:12:00.053 --> 00:12:00.267
That is the ultimate authority, even beyond your peace.

00:12:00.267 --> 00:12:04.720
If the Bible says you can have it, you can.

00:12:04.720 --> 00:12:06.320
If it says don't do it, don't do it.

00:12:09.055 --> 00:12:09.471
It's that simple.

00:12:09.471 --> 00:12:13.067
Fornication and adultery are wrong; the Bible says don't do it.

00:12:13.067 --> 00:12:15.120
Staying pure sexually is all there.

00:12:15.120 --> 00:12:22.368
Following the voice of the Lord for your life—that is the manual we go by.

00:12:22.368 --> 00:12:28.969
When you have the Word and peace combined, it's unfailing; it is the perfect path for your life.

00:12:28.969 --> 00:12:34.800
Whenever it says, "Do not be unequally yoked with unbelievers," it's just God trying to protect you.

00:12:36.205 --> 00:12:46.845
It doesn't matter about the beauty; find a woman or a man who loves the Lord their God with all their heart, mind, soul, and strength.

00:12:49.360 --> 00:12:52.000
Your road is going to be a lot easier.

00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:55.839
It's crucial in these last days.

00:12:55.839 --> 00:13:00.389
If you say, "I don't have anybody like that around me," make your petition unto God.

00:13:07.177 --> 00:13:08.000
Write down what you're believing for: a godly spouse, a house, or whatever.

00:13:15.440 --> 00:13:18.639
Write those things down and make it plain.

00:13:19.120 --> 00:13:29.680
Put it on your refrigerator, your bathroom mirror, or your car visor—someplace where you can see it all the time.

00:13:32.159 --> 00:13:33.706
Let that be a reminder.

00:13:33.973 --> 00:13:37.600
Then pray over it, put your hand on it, and say, "I believe, I receive.

00:13:37.600 --> 00:13:40.480
" Faith calls those things that be not as though they were.

00:13:40.480 --> 00:13:46.220
I believe with all my heart, Father, that You said You supply all my needs according to Your riches in glory by Christ Jesus.

00:13:46.530 --> 00:13:53.199
Every need is not just financial; it's physical, spiritual, mental, and emotional.

00:13:53.199 --> 00:13:57.726
It's whatever you need to operate in abundance until it overflows.

00:14:07.380 --> 00:14:07.690
Growing up, my mom and dad and I would find a house we knew we could afford, go to the property, and lay hands on it.

00:14:10.239 --> 00:14:12.107
We would say, "Father, I thank You that we have favor to find a house like this.

00:14:21.395 --> 00:14:23.540
" I'm not saying go around coveting everyone's houses.

00:14:23.540 --> 00:14:27.257
If it's not for sale, don't do weird stuff.

00:14:27.257 --> 00:14:35.680
But if the house is for sale, say, "Father, I thank You for open doors of opportunity to purchase this home.

00:14:36.320 --> 00:14:45.804
You said You'd give me the desires of my heart, and I thank You that You are the God of more than enough.

00:14:46.480 --> 00:14:50.537
" Lay hands on that piece of land and believe you receive it in the name of Jesus.

00:14:50.834 --> 00:14:51.726
Believe by faith.

00:14:56.663 --> 00:14:57.600
If you feel a leading and the Lord tells you this is your piece of property, stand on the Word.

00:15:05.360 --> 00:15:11.199
Find scriptures that pertain to what you're believing for and use that as your foundation.

00:15:12.799 --> 00:15:13.679
Then find that peace.

00:15:13.839 --> 00:15:15.359
If you don't have peace about it, don't go with it.

00:15:16.560 --> 00:15:19.279
But if you have peace, follow it.

00:15:19.1000 --> 00:15:21.733
We do it all the time.

00:15:21.733 --> 00:15:24.302
"Father, I thank You that You said You provide for us.

00:15:24.302 --> 00:15:30.720
I thank You, God, that You're going to take care of us and do the things You said in Your Word.

00:15:32.000 --> 00:15:33.040
" That's where we stand.

00:15:33.040 --> 00:15:37.457
There were many times in the past when I followed a spirit of heaviness.

00:15:37.457 --> 00:15:43.480
I would be walking around and feel an urge to pray, thinking I had to pray all the time.

00:15:55.600 --> 00:15:56.639
Yeah.

00:15:56.639 --> 00:15:58.139
Because don't you just feel that?

00:15:58.139 --> 00:15:59.040
I used to.

00:15:59.040 --> 00:16:02.183
I felt like impending doom all the time.

00:16:02.183 --> 00:16:04.639
Well, I feel there's a terrorist attack coming.

00:16:04.639 --> 00:16:06.628
I feel this coming and everything.

00:16:06.959 --> 00:16:08.990
Well, you know, I've got to pray over this.

00:16:10.070 --> 00:16:14.309
I feel that there's going to be some kind of major weather event or an earthquake.

00:16:14.309 --> 00:16:20.623
And you walk around in this fear bubble because I'm an intercessor.

00:16:20.623 --> 00:16:22.560
That's supposed to happen; I'm supposed to be praying.

00:16:22.560 --> 00:16:28.399
And the Lord addressed it one day and he told me, 'Brandon, what are you doing?

00:16:28.399 --> 00:16:30.571
' And I said, 'Well, I'm interceding, Lord.

00:16:30.571 --> 00:16:32.506
I said there's a heaviness.

00:16:32.733 --> 00:16:33.1000
You're calling me to pray.

00:16:33.1000 --> 00:16:41.460
' He said, 'No, that is a spirit of forebodings that is tormenting you, Brandon.

00:16:41.460 --> 00:16:46.148
I want you to live life in abundance to the full until it overflows.

00:16:49.519 --> 00:16:49.799
And you are not doing that.

00:16:54.240 --> 00:16:54.640
You are living underneath a dark shadow.

00:16:58.144 --> 00:16:58.840
My yoke is easy and my burden is light.

00:16:58.840 --> 00:17:02.080
' And that's where he was saying to me, 'You're living underneath a burden.

00:17:02.080 --> 00:17:06.205
' And my wife can testify to it; I lived that way.

00:17:08.114 --> 00:17:10.149
I felt like I was in tears all the time walking.

00:17:10.149 --> 00:17:13.473
I'm interceding for somebody, I don't know who it is.

00:17:17.920 --> 00:17:19.108
And I would walk around acting so spiritual, like I was praying all the time at work, at church, or wherever.

00:17:20.355 --> 00:17:22.283
And people would ask, 'Are you okay today, Brother Brandon?

00:17:22.283 --> 00:17:23.466
' 'Oh, no, man.

00:17:23.466 --> 00:17:26.457
I've got the burden to pray.

00:17:26.457 --> 00:17:29.280
I've got a burden to pray.

00:17:29.280 --> 00:17:34.331
' And it sounded like you were doing something so spiritual and it was the flesh.

00:17:34.331 --> 00:17:38.370
It was a demonic spirit tormenting you because fear has torment.

00:17:45.270 --> 00:17:45.475
But perfect love casteth out all fear.

00:17:46.708 --> 00:17:55.648
And I'm telling you, a spirit of forebodings to get on you as a believer because you think you're doing good by thinking you're praying.

00:17:55.648 --> 00:17:59.006
But the Lord wants you to have joy, ladies and gentlemen.

00:18:04.411 --> 00:18:11.700
The Bible said he wants you to have exceedingly abundantly above all that you ask or think, but in joy unspeakable and full of glory.

00:18:26.533 --> 00:18:26.782
The joy of the Lord is our strength.

00:18:26.782 --> 00:18:31.280
There's so many things about joy and walking in peace that passes all understanding.

00:18:31.280 --> 00:18:43.792
So, I just felt in my spirit, because I know a lot of intercessory prayer people follow my channel, that if you walk around with heaviness all the time, check it.

00:18:43.792 --> 00:18:59.306
And this is what I do: 'Father, if this is you praying,' and I question it—I'm just trying to teach you how to do it—'Father, if this is you telling me to intercede for something, then speak on.

00:18:59.306 --> 00:19:09.360
But if this is a spirit of forebodings, a tormenting spirit of fear, I bind it right now in the name of Jesus and I cast you out.

00:19:09.360 --> 00:19:12.960
You get out of here and you leave me alone.

00:19:12.960 --> 00:19:27.520
I will not walk in a spirit of torment and fear, but 2 Timothy 1:7 says that God has not given me a spirit of fear, but of power and of love and of a well-balanced mind, and I will walk in a balanced mind in no fear.

00:19:27.520 --> 00:19:33.074
' So, Father, if this is you and you're warning me to pray about something, then speak on.

00:19:33.074 --> 00:19:39.387
But if it is not, I command this spirit to get out of here now and address it just like that.

00:19:46.080 --> 00:19:53.400
And the moment you start doing that, you'll feel even more of a tug because the Holy Spirit is the one leading you and guiding you into all things.

00:19:53.400 --> 00:19:58.160
He's trying to protect you.

00:19:58.160 --> 00:20:01.289
He wants you to live that life in abundance.

00:20:01.289 --> 00:20:05.200
So he's going to tell you, 'That's me.

00:20:05.200 --> 00:20:06.220
That's me.

00:20:08.746 --> 00:20:09.022
You better pray now.

00:20:09.022 --> 00:20:27.253
Come on, let's jump in the river together,' and you just go in that because then you'll know this is the Holy Spirit really trying to lead me and he's trying to help me because he wants you to follow that peace.

00:20:30.208 --> 00:20:31.840
And so I hope that helped with that.

00:20:31.840 --> 00:20:35.800
I really feel like it's important.

00:20:51.260 --> 00:20:51.530
I feel like I'm talking to somebody about this because the Lord put that on my heart right then to tell you: do not let a spirit of torment push you around.

00:20:52.880 --> 00:20:59.897
You have authority over the devil and you don't have to walk in fear in any area of your life about any calamity.

00:20:59.897 --> 00:21:01.960
We are the victors, not the victims.

00:21:05.230 --> 00:21:06.880
So I want my wife to read this to you.

00:21:06.880 --> 00:21:09.040
This is an amazing book.

00:21:12.540 --> 00:21:12.992
You know, we were at prayer on Sunday at church, which was amazing.

00:21:12.992 --> 00:21:17.039
Every single time we go, we get refilled.

00:21:27.315 --> 00:21:27.520
We go and participate at the Glorious Church Fellowship prayer a lot.

00:21:27.520 --> 00:21:37.920
If you're looking for people that want to jump in the river, we look for it all the time, listening to Lynne Hammond online at Living Word in Minneapolis, Minnesota, and the prayer conference, wanting to grow ourselves spiritually in prayer.

00:21:37.920 --> 00:21:41.623
Pastor Candace leads that prayer group at The Glory's Church, and they're anointed.

00:21:41.623 --> 00:21:46.559
We used to listen to a lot of other prayer groups and we still do.

00:21:46.559 --> 00:21:51.706
But I would encourage everybody, if you want to grow spiritually, you've got to listen to prayer people.

00:21:51.706 --> 00:21:56.587
You've got to feed your spirit just like faith cometh by hearing and hearing by the word of God.

00:21:56.587 --> 00:22:01.639
You've got to feed your spirit so you'll grow in that area and in prayer.

00:22:01.639 --> 00:22:10.119
It's like wanting to learn math and be really good at it, but you never go to math classes.

00:22:10.119 --> 00:22:12.436
Yeah, that's exactly right, babe.

00:22:17.749 --> 00:22:22.132
And then you're taking a spelling class trying to learn math and you're hoping you'll just catch math along the way.

00:22:22.132 --> 00:22:26.240
No, but you never go to math class.

00:22:26.240 --> 00:22:28.629
So, this is where I'm saying we find books.

00:22:28.629 --> 00:22:35.660
When I went to prayer on Sunday, the Lord downloaded so much stuff to me and I walked away.

00:22:35.660 --> 00:22:37.010
I said, 'Hey, babe.

00:22:43.279 --> 00:22:43.599
This is what the Lord said tonight in prayer.

00:22:43.599 --> 00:22:48.960
' And she said, 'That's exactly what he said to me.

00:22:48.960 --> 00:22:53.552
' And it was to help me out with helping this channel and things.

00:22:54.640 --> 00:22:55.200
And the Lord gave her...

00:23:07.920 --> 00:23:08.320
because I said, 'Lord, you're going to have to talk to Diana about this.

00:23:23.970 --> 00:23:24.320
I need your help with that.

00:23:24.320 --> 00:23:30.194
' We flow together on this because I wanted this to flow perfectly.

00:23:30.194 --> 00:23:34.656
And she said, 'He's already told me, hun.

00:23:34.656 --> 00:23:39.480
' She said, 'I heard him to get this book right here.

00:23:39.480 --> 00:23:52.594
' And so this is a book by Brother Hagin, but she was reading these chapters to me, and I want her to read this part right here.

00:23:52.594 --> 00:24:09.520
This is really important and let it minister to y'all because it goes along with what we're trying to teach you all, that Brother Hagin walked this out as a young believer and how he became a spiritual giant in my eyes.

00:24:09.520 --> 00:24:15.679
I mean, I don't see anybody in the natural that heard the Lord as clear in this generation.

00:24:15.679 --> 00:24:16.444
Yeah.

00:24:16.444 --> 00:24:28.195
So he had an open-eyed vision and he saw Jesus come and sit by his bed and he talked to him for an hour and a half.

00:24:28.195 --> 00:24:44.044
And this says Jesus said to me: 'The prophet of the New Testament is very similar to the prophet of the Old Testament in that the prophet of the Old Testament was called a seer because he saw and knew things supernaturally.

00:24:44.933 --> 00:24:47.733
The prophet of the New Testament also sees and knows things supernaturally.

00:24:47.733 --> 00:25:00.159
But the prophet of the New Testament does not have the same status as the prophet of the Old Testament in that I did not set prophets in the church to guide the church.

00:25:03.240 --> 00:25:04.960
A Christian under the New Testament need not seek guidance through prophets.

00:25:21.280 --> 00:25:21.680
He might receive guidance through prophets, but he should not seek it.

00:25:21.680 --> 00:25:24.693
It is unscriptural to do so.

00:25:27.840 --> 00:25:32.900
The ministry of the New Testament prophet in this area is only to confirm what people already have in their own spirits.

00:25:32.900 --> 00:25:41.076
Under the Old Covenant, only the priest, the prophet, and the king were anointed by the Holy Spirit to stand in those offices.

00:25:41.076 --> 00:25:46.311
What you would call the laity did not have the spirit of God upon them or in them.

00:25:46.311 --> 00:25:51.640
Therefore, under the Old Covenant, people would seek guidance through the prophet because he had the spirit of God.

00:25:51.640 --> 00:25:58.542
' Under the New Testament, thanks be to God, we not only have the Spirit of God upon us, we have Him in us.

00:26:00.200 --> 00:26:09.714
Jesus also said to me, 'Under the New Covenant, it does not say, "As many as are led by prophets, they are the sons of God.

00:26:09.714 --> 00:26:17.029
" The New Testament says, "For as many as are led by the Spirit of God, they are the sons of God.

00:26:17.029 --> 00:26:18.263
"' See Romans.

00:26:18.263 --> 00:26:22.666
Get that scripture down inside of you.

00:26:25.806 --> 00:26:26.011
You read that again, baby.

00:26:28.660 --> 00:26:32.360
I love that scripture: 'For as many as are led by the Spirit of God, they are the sons of God.

00:26:32.360 --> 00:26:32.960
' Romans.

00:26:32.960 --> 00:26:45.954
So, you're going to be led by the Spirit of God, and that shows you're a son of God—not led by a prophet, not led by your pastor, but by the Spirit of God.

00:26:45.954 --> 00:26:59.223
Now, He may use your pastor or use a prophetic voice to help you along the way, but it's to confirm some things; ultimately, it's on you by the Spirit of God in you.

00:26:59.223 --> 00:27:00.896
Does that make sense?

00:27:00.896 --> 00:27:03.050
Because that's biblical right there.

00:27:03.050 --> 00:27:03.430
Romans.

00:27:03.430 --> 00:27:10.000
Then He said, 'The number one way, the primary way that I lead all of my children, is by the inward witness.

00:27:10.000 --> 00:27:17.530
' I am going to show you how that works so you won't make the mistakes you have made in the past.

00:27:29.640 --> 00:27:34.620
Then He called my attention to something that had been happening to me for the previous three days.

00:27:37.600 --> 00:27:42.507
For the past three days, I had sat down to write a letter to a pastor confirming a date to hold a meeting for him.

00:27:42.507 --> 00:27:50.520
Somehow, the first day I got about half of a page, and then I tore it up and threw it in the wastebasket.

00:27:53.851 --> 00:27:54.606
The next day I did the same thing.

00:27:56.100 --> 00:27:58.320
The third day I did the same thing.

00:27:58.320 --> 00:28:06.599
Then it was the day that the Lord was here in the room talking to me.

00:28:06.599 --> 00:28:09.066
Jesus said, 'You see me sitting here talking to you.

00:28:17.017 --> 00:28:17.406
This is a manifestation of the Spirit called discerning of spirits.

00:28:17.406 --> 00:28:21.919
' Discerning of spirits is seeing into the spirit realm.

00:28:28.836 --> 00:28:29.084
This is the prophet's ministry in operation.

00:28:32.780 --> 00:28:33.170
You are seeing into the realm of the spirit.

00:28:33.170 --> 00:28:36.760
'You see me, you hear me talking.

00:28:37.989 --> 00:28:43.988
I am bringing you through the vision a word of knowledge and also a word of wisdom.

00:28:50.480 --> 00:28:50.820
I am telling you not to go to that church.

00:28:50.820 --> 00:28:58.045
The pastor would not accept the way that you would minister when you got there.

00:28:58.045 --> 00:29:00.950
But I am never going to lead you this way again.

00:29:00.950 --> 00:29:04.845
' And He never has, and that was many years ago.

00:29:04.845 --> 00:29:09.291
'From now on, I'm going to lead you by the inward witness.

00:29:09.291 --> 00:29:13.646
' You had the inward witness all the time.

00:29:24.170 --> 00:29:24.440
You had a check in your spirit.

00:29:24.440 --> 00:29:28.069
That's the reason you tore up the letter three times.

00:29:34.110 --> 00:29:34.810
You had something on the inside—a check, a red light, a stop signal.

00:29:39.154 --> 00:29:39.817
It wasn't even a voice that said, 'Don't go.

00:29:39.817 --> 00:29:43.840
' It was just an inward intuition.

00:29:43.840 --> 00:29:45.856
Then Jesus reminded me of another invitation.

00:29:45.856 --> 00:29:51.211
I had preached at a convention for one of the Full Gospel denominations the previous year.

00:29:51.211 --> 00:29:56.799
Nearly every pastor there asked me if I could come hold a meeting.

00:30:09.900 --> 00:30:10.240
I had hundreds of calls.

00:30:10.240 --> 00:30:17.547
One fellow came up to me and said, 'Brother Hagin, do you ever go to small churches?

00:30:17.547 --> 00:30:21.467
' I said, 'I go anywhere the Lord says to go.

00:30:21.467 --> 00:30:31.160
' 'Well, we only run about 70 to 90 in Sunday school, but if God ever speaks to you, we want you to come.

00:30:31.160 --> 00:30:34.685
' I dismissed that conversation along with many others.

00:30:34.685 --> 00:30:42.159
Several months later, however, while praying in the church one day about my services that night, that conversation came back to me.

00:30:42.159 --> 00:30:45.520
Then every day it continued to come back to me.

00:30:45.520 --> 00:30:54.080
Finally, after about 30 or 40 days, I said, 'Lord, do you want me to go to that little church for a meeting?

00:30:54.080 --> 00:31:06.304
' The more I would pray about it, the more I would think about it, as we say, the better I would feel about it on the inside of me.

00:31:19.573 --> 00:31:19.876
It wasn't a physical feeling, but it was a feeling in my spirit—peace.

00:31:19.876 --> 00:31:27.499
Jesus, sitting by my bedside, referred to this: 'The more you thought about it, the better you felt about it.

00:31:27.969 --> 00:31:30.260
You had a velvety-like feeling in your spirit.

00:31:30.260 --> 00:31:31.560
That's the green light.

00:31:31.560 --> 00:31:33.200
That's the go-ahead signal.

00:31:33.200 --> 00:31:36.949
That's the witness of the Spirit to go.

00:31:36.949 --> 00:31:45.359
Now you see me sitting here, you hear me talking to you, and I'm telling you to go to that church.

00:31:45.359 --> 00:31:50.130
But I am never going to lead you to go anywhere like this again.

00:31:50.130 --> 00:31:51.538
' He never has.

00:31:51.538 --> 00:31:56.594
'From now on, I'm going to lead you just like I do every other Christian: by the inward witness.

00:31:56.594 --> 00:32:09.555
' Then the Lord said this to me, which is not just for my benefit, but also for yours: 'If you will learn to follow that inward witness, I will make you rich.

00:32:09.555 --> 00:32:15.627
I will guide you in all the affairs of life, financial as well as spiritual.

00:32:15.627 --> 00:32:27.786
' Some think God is only interested in their spiritual well-being and nothing else, but He is interested in everything we are interested in.

00:32:27.786 --> 00:32:34.811
'I am not opposed to my children being rich; I'm opposed to their being covetous.

00:32:34.811 --> 00:32:42.849
' I have followed that inward witness, and He has done just what He said He would do.

00:32:42.849 --> 00:32:44.856
He has made me rich.

00:32:44.856 --> 00:32:47.200
Someone said, 'Are you a millionaire?

00:32:47.200 --> 00:32:48.978
' I didn't say that.

00:32:58.275 --> 00:32:58.559
Some people fail to realize what the word rich means.

00:32:58.559 --> 00:33:01.422
It means a full supply.

00:33:01.422 --> 00:33:03.013
It means abundant provision.

00:33:10.853 --> 00:33:11.102
I have more than a full supply.

00:33:11.600 --> 00:33:13.253
I have more than abundant provision.

00:33:24.799 --> 00:33:25.039
It is because I learned to follow the leading of the Spirit by the inward witness.

00:33:25.039 --> 00:33:29.368
What He did for me, He will do for you.

00:33:29.368 --> 00:33:39.508
It won't come overnight or by the next Saturday night, but as you learn to develop your spirit and follow that inward witness, He will guide you in every area of your life.

00:33:45.680 --> 00:33:45.880
It won't come overnight, but as you develop it, be patient.

00:33:45.880 --> 00:33:52.979
I knew a man down in Texas who had never worn a pair of shoes until he was 12 years old.

00:33:53.249 --> 00:33:58.168
He only had a fifth-grade education, but way back when money was money, he was a millionaire.

00:33:58.168 --> 00:34:10.255
Two different people—one from California and the other from Minnesota—who had been frequent houseguests in his home, told me that this man told each of them the same thing.

00:34:10.255 --> 00:34:18.279
He said to them both, 'In all these years and in all these investments—that's how he made his money—I never lost a dime.

00:34:18.279 --> 00:34:19.609
' That beats my record.

00:34:19.609 --> 00:34:20.609
How about yours?

00:34:20.609 --> 00:34:25.880
'Everything I have ever invested in has made money,' he said to each of them on different occasions.

00:34:25.880 --> 00:34:29.840
Then he told them how he did it: 'I always do this.

00:34:29.840 --> 00:34:35.730
When someone comes along with an idea wanting me to invest in something, my first reaction is mental.

00:34:35.730 --> 00:34:40.120
Now, I know what Jesus said: "When you pray, enter into your closet.

00:34:40.120 --> 00:34:44.170
" He didn't necessarily mean you have to go get into a closet to pray.

00:34:49.310 --> 00:34:51.378
I know He meant for us to shut things out, but I have a large closet in my bedroom where I go to pray.

00:34:54.207 --> 00:34:54.423
I pray about it.

00:34:55.629 --> 00:34:58.651
I wait long enough until I hear what my spirit says.

00:34:58.651 --> 00:35:01.480
Sometimes I wait three days.

00:35:01.480 --> 00:35:06.759
Now, it doesn't mean that I stay in there 24 hours a day.

00:35:11.387 --> 00:35:11.653
I might come out and eat one meal—usually, I miss a few.

00:35:11.653 --> 00:35:23.937
I come out and sleep a little bit, but the majority of the time I am waiting just by myself until I know by an inward witness what I am to do.

00:35:23.937 --> 00:35:30.591
Sometimes my head says, "Boy, you would be a fool to put your money in that; you'll lose your shirt.

00:35:35.488 --> 00:35:35.824
" But my heart says, "Go ahead and invest in it.

00:35:42.520 --> 00:35:42.800
" So I do.

00:35:45.352 --> 00:35:45.520
And in all these years, I have never lost a dime.

00:35:45.520 --> 00:35:53.229
' Then again, someone comes along with a deal and my head says, 'Boy, you better get in on that one.

00:35:53.229 --> 00:35:56.200
' But I don't pay any attention to my head.

00:36:01.599 --> 00:36:01.875
I get in that closet and I wait.

00:36:01.875 --> 00:36:04.079
Sometimes all night long, I wait.

00:36:04.079 --> 00:36:10.240
I'll pray and read my Bible, but a lot of the time I just wait.

00:36:10.610 --> 00:36:14.810
I just get quiet until I hear inside what my heart says.

00:36:14.810 --> 00:36:23.600
When my heart says, 'No, don't do it,' and my head says, 'Yes, you better get in on it,' I don't do it.

00:36:23.600 --> 00:36:25.759
What had this man done?

00:36:25.759 --> 00:36:32.480
He had learned to follow the inward witness, and God had guided him in his business.

00:36:45.627 --> 00:36:45.893
By the late '30s and early '40s, he was already worth two million dollars.

00:36:47.529 --> 00:36:48.951
That doesn't sound big now, but it was then.

00:36:59.320 --> 00:37:05.839
Do you think God loved him more than He loves you?

00:37:05.839 --> 00:37:06.320
No.

00:37:06.320 --> 00:37:08.889
But this man took time to listen to God.

00:37:12.861 --> 00:37:13.119
He took steps and measures to wait upon God.

00:37:13.119 --> 00:37:17.980
The inward witness is just as supernatural as guidance through visions and so on; it is just not as spectacular.

00:37:17.980 --> 00:37:22.937
Many people are looking for the spectacular and they are missing the supernatural that is right there all the time.

00:37:22.937 --> 00:37:23.390
Yeah.

00:37:25.440 --> 00:37:25.680
Do you get it?

00:37:26.400 --> 00:37:28.224
That's what I'm trying to teach y'all.

00:37:28.224 --> 00:37:32.180
It's following that inward peace in your life—that peace that passes all understanding.

00:37:32.180 --> 00:37:38.604
There's so many times people come up to me and say, 'Hey, I believe this thing will help Megan.

00:37:39.230 --> 00:37:42.044
I believe because you know my daughter is overcoming autism.

00:37:42.044 --> 00:37:57.680
' They'll try to come up with some kind of health thing and tell us that this is the cure-all for her and you just put her on this or you put her on that, but my inward peace is not there.

00:38:04.030 --> 00:38:04.280
And I said, 'I do not feel a green light on this.

00:38:05.470 --> 00:38:06.230
I feel this is like snake oil.

00:38:06.230 --> 00:38:08.050
This is not going to work.

00:38:08.050 --> 00:38:18.656
' But Brother Brandon, we've had all this research and all this stuff on it.

00:38:27.280 --> 00:38:27.600
And the Holy Spirit said, 'Don't do that.

00:38:33.599 --> 00:38:33.942
I'm telling you this is not for you.

00:38:33.942 --> 00:38:38.520
' And they say, 'Well, it's changed so many lives.

00:38:38.520 --> 00:38:41.813
' Well, good for them, but that's not for me.

00:38:51.360 --> 00:38:53.200
So, you have to go with the peace over your life.

00:38:53.200 --> 00:39:00.850
They could tell you that it's changed 50,000 people's lives and they're better and everything else has done it and it's the cure-all for them.

00:39:00.850 --> 00:39:08.111
But if you don't have a peace for you, then you follow that inward peace and you pray.

00:39:08.111 --> 00:39:20.747
It's like he went into his closet for two or three days sometimes and would go in there and pray and seek the Lord for himself.

00:39:20.747 --> 00:39:21.813
Everybody is different.

00:39:21.813 --> 00:39:22.693
Nobody's cookie-cutter.

00:39:28.960 --> 00:39:30.575
God did not make cookie-cutter Christians and pull them out and cook them on a sheet and say, 'Look, everybody looks like a gingerbread.

00:39:30.575 --> 00:39:33.520
' Everyone looks different, but we're all different.

00:39:33.520 --> 00:39:34.160
Yeah.

00:39:34.160 --> 00:39:42.840
But we're all made in His image and we all have the Holy Spirit on the inside of us if you're a born-again Christian.

00:39:55.475 --> 00:39:55.813
I believe with all my heart He'll guide each and every single one of us.

00:39:55.813 --> 00:39:58.399
But it's going to be different.

00:40:00.639 --> 00:40:07.870
So you can't get disappointed if He tells you no and you feel like Billy Bob over here was told yes.

00:40:07.870 --> 00:40:10.320
Why'd He tell you no?

00:40:14.270 --> 00:40:14.580
I don't know.

00:40:23.529 --> 00:40:23.973
Just follow the peace of God for you and whatever you feel in your heart, do it with all your heart, mind, soul, and strength.

00:40:26.133 --> 00:40:30.960
I had one lady say, 'I hear all these people talking about investing in gold and silver, but the Lord told me not to do it.

00:40:46.600 --> 00:40:47.050
What do you think that's about?

00:40:47.050 --> 00:40:49.429
Should I do it?

00:40:49.429 --> 00:40:57.337
' I said, 'No, if the Holy Spirit told you not to do it, then don't do it.

00:40:57.337 --> 00:40:59.084
' I can't answer for you.

00:41:02.231 --> 00:41:14.150
I just know that that's what the Holy Spirit has told certain people and they may say, 'Hey, I took hundreds of thousands of dollars and invested in gold and silver,' and then the Lord said, 'Don't do that for you.

00:41:14.150 --> 00:41:15.760
' I can't question that.

00:41:24.284 --> 00:41:24.480
You have to follow your peace.

00:41:24.480 --> 00:41:27.280
I think that's the best.

00:41:46.160 --> 00:41:46.382
You will never ever miss it if you follow the peace.

00:41:47.938 --> 00:41:52.731
This is one thing: we tried to fleece God once, and a lot of people try to fleece God.

00:41:52.731 --> 00:42:06.080
They say, you know, like Gideon, Gideon put the fleece out there and did all that he did and the Lord used it to help him.

00:42:06.080 --> 00:42:14.120
But Gideon didn't have the Holy Spirit dwelling on the inside of him like we have.

00:42:14.120 --> 00:42:15.947
That was Old Covenant.

00:42:18.971 --> 00:42:21.770
And so, under the New Covenant now, you can put out a fleece and get fleeced real quick.

00:42:21.770 --> 00:42:27.408
But I've done it, and I'm not recommending anybody else do it, but I did it.

00:42:32.047 --> 00:42:47.520
I told the Lord whenever we were starting out to go full-time doing eBay and Poshmark, and then I felt the Holy Spirit say, 'I want you to tell Diana it's time for her to move on from the church doing accounting there and I want you to go full-time into this.

00:42:47.520 --> 00:42:51.022
' And I thought, 'Oh man.

00:42:51.022 --> 00:42:54.027
' I never told her at all.

00:42:54.027 --> 00:43:03.680
I was scared actually because I said, 'Man, I like the security of every two weeks having something.

00:43:03.680 --> 00:43:10.971
' The Lord said, 'Brandon, you're asking me for increase and I'm trying to bring increase to you.

00:43:10.971 --> 00:43:13.806
You've got to let go.

00:43:13.806 --> 00:43:15.817
' It's like an acrobat.

00:43:16.114 --> 00:43:28.389
A trapeze artist grabs on to the next thing, but you don't want to let go of what's behind you because it's comfortable.

00:43:28.389 --> 00:43:41.635
You've got to sometimes let go and grab on by faith to the next thing so that God can take you from glory to glory.

00:43:41.635 --> 00:43:47.560
But many times we latch on to what's behind us and we don't want to let go of it.

00:43:47.560 --> 00:43:55.533
But God's saying go out and grab on to the next thing.

00:43:55.533 --> 00:43:59.982
You're going to have to do some things by faith.

00:44:12.106 --> 00:44:12.613
And it may make your flesh feel uncomfortable to do what I've asked you to do.

00:44:12.613 --> 00:44:16.240
But you've got to be obedient.

00:44:29.622 --> 00:44:30.056
And sometimes you're just going to have to do it blindly.

00:44:30.056 --> 00:44:34.720
Just do what He tells you to do and do it by faith.

00:44:34.720 --> 00:44:54.586
If He says do it, well, I don't see how it makes any sense, and you grab on to it and you swing out and you're in a better position than what you were because you stepped out by faith.

00:45:04.343 --> 00:45:04.720
And that's where we were.

00:45:17.245 --> 00:45:17.634
I didn't want to step out.

00:45:17.634 --> 00:45:21.400
She didn't know the Lord was dealing with me this way.

00:45:21.400 --> 00:45:41.373
But I told Him, I said, 'Lord, if this is you, then let there be four inches of rain,' because I know in Oklahoma in the middle of summer, we don't get a lot of rain.

00:45:46.570 --> 00:45:46.960
It's dry a lot of times.

00:45:46.960 --> 00:45:52.960
So I was trying to make it really hard.

00:45:52.960 --> 00:45:59.280
I thought, 'Lord, I'm going to make this one unmistakable.

